1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:37,000
( Watch on www.kissasia.co, .club, .be, .org, .net, .id, .xyz )

2
00:00:39,145 --> 00:00:40,675
(All characters, places,
and organizations are fictional.)

3
00:00:40,675 --> 00:00:41,975
(Children were filmed
under production guidelines.)

4
00:00:43,285 --> 00:00:45,185
(Episode 1)

5
00:01:03,565 --> 00:01:05,205
(Surgery in progress)

6
00:01:36,865 --> 00:01:38,305
Call 911! Hurry!

7
00:01:38,435 --> 00:01:40,005
- Momo, stay with me!
- What happened?

8
00:01:40,475 --> 00:01:42,505
What do we do? Manager Oh!

9
00:01:51,015 --> 00:01:52,485
It isn't love if it changes.

10
00:01:54,415 --> 00:01:55,415
You have to stay...

11
00:01:57,425 --> 00:01:58,725
by my side forever.

12
00:02:00,255 --> 00:02:01,495
- Momo!
- Momo.

13
00:02:01,495 --> 00:02:02,565
- Momo!
- Yes, we need you here right away. Hurry.

14
00:02:02,625 --> 00:02:03,665
There was a scuba diving accident!

15
00:02:13,275 --> 00:02:14,305
Director Shin.

16
00:02:15,105 --> 00:02:17,175
Momo has lost consciousness on a boat.

17
00:02:24,085 --> 00:02:25,985
- Did they call 911?
- Yes, they called for help.

18
00:02:35,925 --> 00:02:37,425
(International Arrivals)

19
00:02:37,495 --> 00:02:39,265
(New York: Arrived)

20
00:02:40,095 --> 00:02:41,295
What's taking so long?

21
00:02:42,135 --> 00:02:43,405
- Here they come!
- Finally.

22
00:02:46,005 --> 00:02:47,005
Here they come!

23
00:02:47,835 --> 00:02:49,345
I wish they would come out soon.

24
00:02:51,675 --> 00:02:52,675
I hope they come out soon.

25
00:02:52,675 --> 00:02:54,645
Come on, why aren't they coming out?

26
00:02:56,715 --> 00:02:57,745
Welcome back.

27
00:02:59,215 --> 00:03:00,885
Who is all this for? Is it a celebrity?

28
00:03:01,285 --> 00:03:03,385
Looks like it.
But they won't tell me who, though.

29
00:03:03,525 --> 00:03:05,085
It can't be for Momo.

30
00:03:08,195 --> 00:03:09,195
Hello.

31
00:03:10,695 --> 00:03:12,765
We met once before
at an exhibition with Momo.

32
00:03:13,065 --> 00:03:14,335
I'm with the culture desk
at Sungwoo Daily.

33
00:03:15,065 --> 00:03:17,105
- Oh, yes...
- I'm Geum Ba Ra.

34
00:03:18,135 --> 00:03:20,235
That's right. You have a unique name.

35
00:03:21,475 --> 00:03:22,875
Are you here for me?

36
00:03:23,875 --> 00:03:26,375
TEN.CO is arriving
a day ahead of schedule.

37
00:03:27,215 --> 00:03:28,215
"Tango?"

38
00:03:28,215 --> 00:03:30,685
It's TEN.CO, the popular idol group.

39
00:03:31,715 --> 00:03:32,715
I see.

40
00:03:33,915 --> 00:03:37,455
I'm having dinner with Momo tonight,
but her phone is off.

41
00:03:37,555 --> 00:03:38,755
Her manager isn't picking up either.

42
00:03:39,225 --> 00:03:42,125
I'm going to be about an hour late
because of TEN.CO's arrival.

43
00:03:43,725 --> 00:03:45,195
With Momo? Just the two of you?

44
00:03:45,635 --> 00:03:47,795
Yes. She said she had an exclusive for me.

45
00:03:48,435 --> 00:03:50,505
If you can reach her another way,

46
00:03:50,505 --> 00:03:52,575
could you ask her to delay dinner an hour?

47
00:03:52,635 --> 00:03:54,275
- It's TEN.CO!
- Where? Where are they?

48
00:03:58,475 --> 00:03:59,475
I'd really appreciate it.

49
00:04:04,385 --> 00:04:05,715
Let's get some pictures!

50
00:04:08,915 --> 00:04:12,455
The person you have called is unavailable.
Leave a message after the tone.

51
00:04:12,555 --> 00:04:13,725
Is she filming something?

52
00:04:15,325 --> 00:04:16,925
Ever since she got engaged,

53
00:04:17,565 --> 00:04:18,995
she can't even be bothered
to text me once a day.

54
00:04:19,065 --> 00:04:20,365
(Manager Oh)

55
00:04:25,775 --> 00:04:27,735
It's ringing, but he's not picking up.

56
00:04:30,305 --> 00:04:31,775
Why isn't anyone answering?

57
00:04:32,845 --> 00:04:34,445
Do you happen to know
Momo's schedule today?

58
00:04:35,445 --> 00:04:36,445
No, I don't.

59
00:04:36,745 --> 00:04:38,215
(Director Choi Do Il)

60
00:04:41,815 --> 00:04:44,025
Yes, CEO Hyun. It's been a while.

61
00:04:44,025 --> 00:04:45,655
Why isn't Momo's manager...

62
00:04:46,095 --> 00:04:47,595
answering my calls?

63
00:04:48,025 --> 00:04:49,425
And I don't have
the road manager's number.

64
00:04:49,525 --> 00:04:51,795
Really? I'm in Taiwan right now.

65
00:04:52,735 --> 00:04:53,835
You're a busy man.

66
00:04:53,895 --> 00:04:56,205
Anyway, I just met a reporter
from Sungwoo Daily,

67
00:04:56,365 --> 00:04:58,765
and she said Momo promised her
some kind of surprise scoop today.

68
00:04:59,175 --> 00:05:00,705
I'm worried she'll announce
the engagement.

69
00:05:00,705 --> 00:05:01,905
She's close to that reporter.

70
00:05:01,975 --> 00:05:05,205
Exactly. It's too soon.
The wedding isn't until next year.

71
00:05:05,275 --> 00:05:06,715
Right. I'll look into it.

72
00:05:07,015 --> 00:05:08,875
Isn't she with Director Shin Ju Shin?

73
00:05:09,015 --> 00:05:11,445
Director Shin? Free at this hour?

74
00:05:13,015 --> 00:05:14,015
Hello?

75
00:05:18,455 --> 00:05:19,595
My battery died.

76
00:05:38,805 --> 00:05:39,815
Yes?

77
00:05:40,415 --> 00:05:41,845
Is Momo home?

78
00:05:42,245 --> 00:05:43,245
No, she's not.

79
00:05:43,685 --> 00:05:44,685
What are you doing?

80
00:05:45,015 --> 00:05:46,715
She went scuba diving.

81
00:05:46,715 --> 00:05:48,915
Not Momo. What are you doing?

82
00:05:49,985 --> 00:05:50,985
Me?

83
00:05:52,695 --> 00:05:55,195
- Cleaning.
- You sound like you just woke up.

84
00:05:55,595 --> 00:05:57,465
I haven't said a word all day.

85
00:05:59,765 --> 00:06:01,135
Are you back already?

86
00:06:01,135 --> 00:06:03,135
I thought you weren't arriving
until 9:30 p.m.

87
00:06:03,205 --> 00:06:04,335
I'm on my way. I'm hanging up.

88
00:06:06,275 --> 00:06:07,775
(Manager Oh)

89
00:06:09,745 --> 00:06:11,875
- Yes?
- It's me.

90
00:06:12,145 --> 00:06:13,145
Where's Momo?

91
00:06:15,645 --> 00:06:16,685
Isn't she with you?

92
00:06:18,245 --> 00:06:20,655
She should be on her way to Seoul.
I heard she went scuba diving.

93
00:06:20,915 --> 00:06:22,385
There's been a problem.

94
00:06:22,785 --> 00:06:24,925
- We're at Gangwon Hospital.
- What's wrong?

95
00:06:27,055 --> 00:06:28,155
Is Momo hurt?

96
00:06:28,955 --> 00:06:31,865
(TEN.CO arrives a day early
for domestic schedule.)

97
00:06:45,375 --> 00:06:47,845
They said something had suddenly come up
with Momo.

98
00:06:50,485 --> 00:06:53,215
- The A course, please.
- Okay, and coffee to go with it?

99
00:06:53,285 --> 00:06:54,855
Yes, a latte today.

100
00:06:54,855 --> 00:06:55,855
Got it.

101
00:06:56,725 --> 00:06:59,295
Does CEO Ha come here once in a while?

102
00:06:59,725 --> 00:07:00,995
Which CEO Ha?

103
00:07:01,395 --> 00:07:03,425
- James?
- CEO Ha Yong Joong.

104
00:07:03,495 --> 00:07:05,625
Yes. He was here earlier today.

105
00:07:35,865 --> 00:07:36,865
Aren't you scared?

106
00:07:39,335 --> 00:07:40,835
You once said...

107
00:07:41,835 --> 00:07:44,105
that there was nothing left
for us to be afraid of.

108
00:07:45,765 --> 00:07:48,375
I'm sleeping over tonight.

109
00:07:49,505 --> 00:07:50,605
Is that okay?

110
00:07:51,345 --> 00:07:52,375
You don't want me to?

111
00:07:53,045 --> 00:07:55,345
So is Momo at the director's hospital?

112
00:07:55,945 --> 00:07:57,315
If a story gets out, it'll be a disaster.

113
00:08:02,215 --> 00:08:03,855
Yes, this is Kim Jin Ju.

114
00:08:31,785 --> 00:08:35,055
(6 Months Before Momo's Accident)

115
00:08:53,505 --> 00:08:54,575
CEO Ha...

116
00:08:55,575 --> 00:08:56,605
Yong Joong?

117
00:09:04,285 --> 00:09:05,285
Right.

118
00:09:07,185 --> 00:09:09,385
Is the terrace okay?

119
00:09:11,755 --> 00:09:14,455
- This is our cameraman.
- I see.

120
00:09:14,795 --> 00:09:15,855
I'm Lee Jin Ho.

121
00:09:16,665 --> 00:09:19,395
- I don't have a business card yet.
- I see.

122
00:09:29,445 --> 00:09:30,645
You must be new.

123
00:09:31,105 --> 00:09:32,945
I joined the company the year before last.

124
00:09:35,375 --> 00:09:36,985
You live in a nice neighborhood.

125
00:09:38,415 --> 00:09:39,615
I like being near the water.

126
00:09:41,415 --> 00:09:43,425
But I'd rather not take any photos.

127
00:09:43,755 --> 00:09:46,325
It's for an interview,
so it's a bit difficult without a photo.

128
00:09:46,455 --> 00:09:50,695
I made it clear to CEO Lee Myeong Woo
that I didn't do photos.

129
00:09:50,795 --> 00:09:52,695
That wasn't relayed to me.

130
00:09:53,335 --> 00:09:55,195
Don't you know CEO Lee personally?

131
00:09:55,735 --> 00:09:59,235
He's close with a senior colleague.
I've joined them for a meal before.

132
00:10:01,175 --> 00:10:03,105
How about a caricature?

133
00:10:04,045 --> 00:10:05,575
I'm not a politician.

134
00:10:05,845 --> 00:10:08,115
So, drinks first? Coffee, maybe?

135
00:10:08,175 --> 00:10:09,585
Ginger ale, please.

136
00:10:09,645 --> 00:10:11,615
- I've had an iced coffee this morning.
- Okay.

137
00:10:13,815 --> 00:10:15,615
Does everyone just drink coffee
by default?

138
00:10:16,025 --> 00:10:17,985
Sorry. But to be honest, yes.

139
00:10:17,985 --> 00:10:20,255
Most people I meet,
and all my colleagues do.

140
00:10:20,395 --> 00:10:21,895
If you don't want it to be just text,

141
00:10:22,425 --> 00:10:24,565
how about an image of the Karuan Serpan
from the game?

142
00:10:33,035 --> 00:10:34,935
Hey, why are you crying?

143
00:10:36,875 --> 00:10:37,905
Where's your mom?

144
00:10:39,305 --> 00:10:41,545
Did you lose her? Are you all alone?

145
00:10:42,785 --> 00:10:45,315
Don't cry. I'll help you get home.

146
00:10:46,455 --> 00:10:47,655
Did you come here to buy a snack?

147
00:10:48,715 --> 00:10:49,825
(Neighborhood Supermarket)

148
00:10:49,855 --> 00:10:50,855
What's your name?

149
00:10:52,695 --> 00:10:53,825
Ba Ra.

150
00:10:54,425 --> 00:10:55,455
Ba Ra?

151
00:10:56,025 --> 00:10:57,195
Your name is Ba Ra?

152
00:10:58,865 --> 00:11:00,435
How old are you? Five?

153
00:11:01,565 --> 00:11:02,565
Six?

154
00:11:04,735 --> 00:11:07,035
First, let me buy you something.

155
00:11:12,045 --> 00:11:13,615
(Neighborhood Supermarket)

156
00:11:35,035 --> 00:11:36,135
Let's go!

157
00:11:49,445 --> 00:11:51,815
- What are you doing here?
- I came to see you.

158
00:11:54,555 --> 00:11:55,715
You never said you had a younger sibling.

159
00:11:59,625 --> 00:12:02,095
Draw your parents' faces accurately.

160
00:12:02,095 --> 00:12:03,595
- Okay.
- Yes, teacher.

161
00:12:03,965 --> 00:12:05,265
All right, you may begin.

162
00:12:12,205 --> 00:12:15,575
Gosh! Look at that.
You did a great job, Beom Tak.

163
00:12:16,345 --> 00:12:17,445
Good job, Ha Neul.

164
00:12:19,375 --> 00:12:20,375
What is this?

165
00:12:21,945 --> 00:12:23,915
Geum Ba Ra, you can't leave
until you finish your drawing.

166
00:12:25,515 --> 00:12:26,955
She has to stay after and finish.

167
00:12:27,315 --> 00:12:28,615
- Won't that emotionally scar her?
- I think so.

168
00:12:31,985 --> 00:12:34,295
Your homeroom teacher did that,
even though he knew?

169
00:12:36,895 --> 00:12:37,895
Are you done?

170
00:12:45,005 --> 00:12:46,875
Are you being defiant? To your teacher?

171
00:12:47,335 --> 00:12:49,745
You must've had caregivers
at the orphanage.

172
00:12:50,745 --> 00:12:53,845
But they're not my mom and dad.

173
00:12:55,675 --> 00:12:56,815
You're always talking back.

174
00:12:57,085 --> 00:12:58,885
You learned only bad habits there.

175
00:13:00,555 --> 00:13:01,585
Are you crying?

176
00:13:01,985 --> 00:13:03,255
What good is crying?

177
00:13:03,655 --> 00:13:05,025
Does it feel unfair?

178
00:13:05,455 --> 00:13:06,625
That bastard...

179
00:13:06,695 --> 00:13:08,195
How could someone like him be...

180
00:13:11,495 --> 00:13:13,365
- Go on and have some.
- What, you don't have hands?

181
00:13:13,435 --> 00:13:14,465
What are you, a baby?

182
00:13:15,165 --> 00:13:17,035
She is a baby.
Who would think she's a fourth grader?

183
00:13:18,035 --> 00:13:19,405
I thought she was in kindergarten.

184
00:13:25,605 --> 00:13:29,215
(Apprenticeship Training Center)

185
00:13:29,275 --> 00:13:31,985
(Shin Ju Shin)

186
00:13:36,055 --> 00:13:37,155
Stop for a second.

187
00:13:42,425 --> 00:13:43,765
(Apprenticeship Training Center)

188
00:13:44,695 --> 00:13:45,695
Get in.

189
00:13:46,095 --> 00:13:48,235
- I'm not going home.
- You wouldn't be.

190
00:13:49,605 --> 00:13:51,165
Why isn't Ji An Hee coming to school?
What's he up to?

191
00:13:53,235 --> 00:13:54,505
You shouldn't be hanging out with him.

192
00:13:55,175 --> 00:13:56,175
Can't you tell?

193
00:13:56,745 --> 00:13:58,605
He's not the punk you think he is.

194
00:13:59,345 --> 00:14:00,345
Just go.

195
00:14:09,485 --> 00:14:11,085
(Seongsil Hall)

196
00:14:12,525 --> 00:14:13,525
Aren't you going to college?

197
00:14:19,465 --> 00:14:20,765
Okay, thank you for your hard work.

198
00:15:27,795 --> 00:15:29,395
Just be quiet and listen.

199
00:15:30,965 --> 00:15:32,065
That was one of the parents, wasn't it?

200
00:15:32,365 --> 00:15:34,405
The young woman you were dining with
at Mangyeongru.

201
00:15:35,275 --> 00:15:36,545
I just took a wild guess.

202
00:15:37,275 --> 00:15:39,845
Everyone knows
you shouldn't accept gifts like that.

203
00:15:40,615 --> 00:15:42,175
Are you the only one who doesn't know,
Mr. Kim?

204
00:15:43,145 --> 00:15:44,585
Just give me one answer, and I'll go.

205
00:15:44,985 --> 00:15:46,785
What kind of educator are you
to these kids?

206
00:15:49,855 --> 00:15:51,525
I asked, what kind of teacher are you?

207
00:15:54,525 --> 00:15:57,495
I like the kids, and I love them...

208
00:15:58,095 --> 00:16:00,535
- I do my best to...
- You do your best to discriminate?

209
00:16:03,005 --> 00:16:04,605
You need to change, starting now.

210
00:16:04,935 --> 00:16:07,205
No more discrimination.
Treat every kid equally,

211
00:16:07,275 --> 00:16:09,275
whether they have wealthy parents
or come from nothing.

212
00:16:09,905 --> 00:16:11,005
Do you understand what I'm saying?

213
00:16:11,905 --> 00:16:13,615
- Do you?
- Yes.

214
00:16:15,715 --> 00:16:17,385
How can you, a homeroom teacher,
hurt your students?

215
00:16:18,215 --> 00:16:21,455
You're raising two daughters yourself,
So Young and Hye Young.

216
00:16:22,585 --> 00:16:24,555
I wonder what would happen
if I sent this to the school board?

217
00:16:24,955 --> 00:16:27,895
I got a clear shot of the parent's face
and of you accepting the gift.

218
00:16:29,625 --> 00:16:31,595
This looks like
some very expensive liquor, too.

219
00:16:32,365 --> 00:16:33,365
So?

220
00:16:34,795 --> 00:16:36,035
What about the game's format?

221
00:16:36,735 --> 00:16:39,035
It's a side-scrolling platformer.

222
00:16:40,435 --> 00:16:41,475
Have you never played one before?

223
00:16:43,105 --> 00:16:45,005
This is for our readers
who might not be familiar.

224
00:16:45,945 --> 00:16:48,315
Could you briefly explain the plot for us?

225
00:16:49,115 --> 00:16:51,285
You acquire powers
hidden across the continent...

226
00:16:51,645 --> 00:16:52,985
to save the princess.

227
00:16:53,315 --> 00:16:54,515
Yes, sir. Alright.

228
00:16:54,715 --> 00:16:57,785
The game's protagonist, Karuan,
is a very charming character.

229
00:16:58,125 --> 00:17:00,155
Does he resemble you,
the developer, at all?

230
00:17:03,025 --> 00:17:04,025
Do you think so?

231
00:17:05,725 --> 00:17:06,865
Have you seen comments...

232
00:17:06,865 --> 00:17:10,465
from fans asking
if Karuan is your avatar, CEO Ha?

233
00:17:11,205 --> 00:17:12,205
No, I haven't.

234
00:17:12,865 --> 00:17:14,405
He was just created to be a fun...

235
00:17:15,035 --> 00:17:16,605
and cool character.

236
00:17:17,845 --> 00:17:21,075
Three and a half million sold worldwide
in a month is a record...

237
00:17:21,075 --> 00:17:22,575
no one in the country has.

238
00:17:24,385 --> 00:17:26,285
How does that feel?

239
00:17:26,655 --> 00:17:28,085
It deserves a grand finish.

240
00:17:29,555 --> 00:17:31,155
Would you say you're ambitious?

241
00:17:31,425 --> 00:17:33,195
Is there anyone who isn't?

242
00:17:34,295 --> 00:17:35,725
Have you met anyone who isn't?

243
00:17:37,195 --> 00:17:39,365
It's admirable, as long as it's not greed.

244
00:17:42,435 --> 00:17:44,165
I did some research,

245
00:17:45,065 --> 00:17:46,935
and it says you dropped out
of high school.

246
00:17:47,505 --> 00:17:50,345
- That's right.
- May I ask why?

247
00:17:51,105 --> 00:17:52,845
I just wasn't into studying.

248
00:17:54,075 --> 00:17:57,415
And was there any particular reason
you weren't interested?

249
00:17:59,015 --> 00:18:01,055
Just like you don't need a reason
to like something,

250
00:18:01,515 --> 00:18:02,785
I just didn't want to do it.

251
00:18:03,725 --> 00:18:05,725
You seem very straightforward and cool.

252
00:18:05,855 --> 00:18:07,325
I like to keep things simple.

253
00:18:07,925 --> 00:18:10,525
Is it because game development
requires so much brainpower?

254
00:18:10,765 --> 00:18:11,795
That's part of it.

255
00:18:12,695 --> 00:18:15,695
How do you relieve stress?
Do you work out?

256
00:18:16,095 --> 00:18:17,205
Do I look like the type?

257
00:18:19,265 --> 00:18:22,175
You're in great shape. I'd say you do.

258
00:18:22,175 --> 00:18:24,105
Yes. I work out at home too.

259
00:18:25,175 --> 00:18:26,675
I run for one hour every morning.

260
00:18:28,445 --> 00:18:29,915
Here at the Han River Park?

261
00:18:30,245 --> 00:18:33,315
Yes. I sometimes catch the sunrise, too.

262
00:18:34,555 --> 00:18:35,855
You're so disciplined.

263
00:18:42,025 --> 00:18:43,025
Is working out...

264
00:18:45,025 --> 00:18:47,935
enough to give you your dopamine fix?

265
00:18:49,065 --> 00:18:51,435
Are you asking
if I do anything else for fun?

266
00:18:51,935 --> 00:18:52,935
It's just that...

267
00:18:53,535 --> 00:18:55,975
it's rare for people to work out
just for the fun of it.

268
00:18:56,605 --> 00:18:58,875
Some people genuinely love to study,

269
00:18:59,375 --> 00:19:02,075
but most of us force ourselves
to work out just to stay healthy.

270
00:19:02,815 --> 00:19:04,345
So I was wondering...

271
00:19:04,415 --> 00:19:06,345
if you did anything else
to blow off steam.

272
00:19:09,555 --> 00:19:12,455
People throw that word "dopamine"
around a lot these days,

273
00:19:12,825 --> 00:19:13,855
but what is it exactly?

274
00:19:14,295 --> 00:19:16,395
It's a precursor hormone to adrenaline.

275
00:19:16,725 --> 00:19:20,895
It's released when you eat good food
or do something you enjoy.

276
00:19:22,095 --> 00:19:23,365
And in your case?

277
00:19:24,105 --> 00:19:25,135
When do you...

278
00:19:25,865 --> 00:19:26,935
For me,

279
00:19:27,575 --> 00:19:29,335
it's when an interview is going well.

280
00:19:29,875 --> 00:19:32,205
When a short question gets a long answer,

281
00:19:32,275 --> 00:19:33,615
my dopamine spikes.

282
00:19:35,315 --> 00:19:37,245
But too much of it isn't a good thing.

283
00:20:38,075 --> 00:20:39,205
You're a new face.

284
00:20:41,845 --> 00:20:43,445
- Special Forces?
- UDT, sir.

285
00:20:43,515 --> 00:20:44,585
You've got a good look about you.

286
00:20:45,185 --> 00:20:46,185
Thank you, sir.

287
00:20:47,885 --> 00:20:48,955
- Hey.
- Hey.

288
00:20:49,015 --> 00:20:50,025
I'm not late, am I?

289
00:20:52,055 --> 00:20:54,525
Manager Kang, the Chairman's watch is off.

290
00:20:54,525 --> 00:20:55,625
Is it five minutes off?

291
00:21:00,895 --> 00:21:02,795
- What about Su Ah?
- She got back yesterday.

292
00:21:03,335 --> 00:21:04,635
I heard she has a boyfriend?

293
00:21:04,635 --> 00:21:07,205
Yes, but she says he's a guy friend.

294
00:21:07,435 --> 00:21:10,445
What's all this "guy friend,"
"boyfriend" nonsense?

295
00:21:10,675 --> 00:21:12,645
As opposed to what, dating an animal?

296
00:21:14,715 --> 00:21:17,415
Kids these days are so different
from when we were young.

297
00:21:17,515 --> 00:21:18,945
She really cleaned me out.

298
00:21:19,845 --> 00:21:23,685
That one runs circles
around her older brother.

299
00:21:23,885 --> 00:21:25,885
The Ha women are a tough bunch.

300
00:21:26,155 --> 00:21:29,255
- Stronger than us men.
- That's not true for you, Mr. Chairman.

301
00:21:30,225 --> 00:21:31,265
Come on.

302
00:21:32,265 --> 00:21:33,295
And lastly,

303
00:21:35,035 --> 00:21:37,465
could you tell us about your future plans?

304
00:21:38,135 --> 00:21:40,105
I'll be continuously developing DLC...

305
00:21:40,405 --> 00:21:43,345
to keep providing our players
with great new content.

306
00:21:43,775 --> 00:21:46,345
But first,
I'm going to take a trip to recharge.

307
00:21:47,015 --> 00:21:48,215
DLC?

308
00:21:48,415 --> 00:21:49,815
Downloadable content.

309
00:21:58,825 --> 00:21:59,855
Thank you for your time.

310
00:22:00,625 --> 00:22:01,695
Is that it?

311
00:22:02,355 --> 00:22:04,795
- Yes.
- You're a very fast typer.

312
00:22:05,295 --> 00:22:06,425
I bet you're good at video games.

313
00:22:14,135 --> 00:22:17,045
Can I ask you a personal question?

314
00:22:18,905 --> 00:22:19,905
Sure.

315
00:22:20,975 --> 00:22:23,015
Since you work mostly by yourself,

316
00:22:23,645 --> 00:22:25,445
don't you ever get lonely?

317
00:22:28,915 --> 00:22:30,255
I don't have time to be lonely.

318
00:22:32,785 --> 00:22:35,855
How many close friends do you have
that you can confide in?

319
00:22:37,195 --> 00:22:38,325
They're all busy, I guess.

320
00:22:39,595 --> 00:22:42,865
I guess you could say everyday happiness
wasn't meant for me.

321
00:22:44,565 --> 00:22:46,835
Now, I'd like to try living
like everyone else.

322
00:22:49,635 --> 00:22:50,875
Where are you traveling to?

323
00:22:51,145 --> 00:22:52,945
Europe, starting with Italy.

324
00:22:54,015 --> 00:22:55,275
Do you have a favorite place in Europe?

325
00:22:55,775 --> 00:22:56,915
I'm not sure.

326
00:22:57,885 --> 00:23:00,555
Personally,
I've always wanted to go to Paris.

327
00:23:01,555 --> 00:23:02,985
You haven't been to Paris yet?

328
00:23:03,485 --> 00:23:04,485
No.

329
00:23:07,655 --> 00:23:09,125
The two of you have such a great vibe.

330
00:23:09,655 --> 00:23:10,995
Do you mind if I get a shot of you two?

331
00:23:11,265 --> 00:23:13,565
It's not for an article.
Just to remember the interview.

332
00:23:15,695 --> 00:23:16,695
By the way,

333
00:23:17,765 --> 00:23:19,635
for the Head of Strategic Planning
at the holding company,

334
00:23:20,275 --> 00:23:22,275
I'm going to recommend Bae Seon Gil.

335
00:23:23,205 --> 00:23:24,205
I...

336
00:23:25,475 --> 00:23:27,545
was thinking of Min Kang Woo.

337
00:23:28,745 --> 00:23:29,745
Bae Seon Gil.

338
00:23:29,745 --> 00:23:32,885
Chairman, Min Kang Woo's the best
in all aspects.

339
00:23:33,215 --> 00:23:34,255
Why are you so...

340
00:23:35,115 --> 00:23:36,385
protective of Min Kang Woo?

341
00:23:36,825 --> 00:23:37,855
It's not that I'm being protective.

342
00:23:37,925 --> 00:23:41,695
Think of Bae Seon Gil's accomplishments,
like landing the Dubai contract.

343
00:23:42,495 --> 00:23:44,525
He dedicated his life to this company,
and it cost him his marriage.

344
00:23:44,595 --> 00:23:46,125
He didn't dedicate himself to the company.

345
00:23:46,425 --> 00:23:48,495
He got divorced because
he dedicated his body to a younger woman.

346
00:23:48,835 --> 00:23:49,895
And he got caught red-handed.

347
00:23:51,135 --> 00:23:52,835
Are you spying on our executives?

348
00:23:53,535 --> 00:23:54,605
Informal?

349
00:23:54,605 --> 00:23:57,675
What is this, political scheming
or corporate manipulation?

350
00:23:58,245 --> 00:23:59,705
You cut me off while I was speaking...

351
00:24:01,245 --> 00:24:02,315
I apologize.

352
00:24:02,315 --> 00:24:04,045
It's just like last time
with Woojin Shipping.

353
00:24:04,045 --> 00:24:05,245
Your right-hand man took the position.

354
00:24:05,385 --> 00:24:07,955
Stop with the "right-hand man" talk.

355
00:24:07,955 --> 00:24:09,385
- What?
- If that's how you label it,

356
00:24:09,385 --> 00:24:11,225
then Bae Seon Gil is
your right-hand man, Mr. Chairman.

357
00:24:11,285 --> 00:24:13,185
Team Leader Bae may be a great salesman,

358
00:24:13,385 --> 00:24:16,025
but this position requires a strategist.

359
00:24:16,095 --> 00:24:17,365
Are you lecturing me now?

360
00:24:17,365 --> 00:24:19,195
In terms of contributions,
performance reviews,

361
00:24:19,495 --> 00:24:22,265
and every other evaluation standard,
Min Kang Woo is the right choice.

362
00:24:22,265 --> 00:24:23,435
Why, you little...

363
00:24:23,635 --> 00:24:24,635
Brother.

364
00:24:24,705 --> 00:24:26,365
Just because you studied abroad,

365
00:24:26,365 --> 00:24:27,835
you think you can talk down to me?

366
00:24:28,005 --> 00:24:29,175
You have no sense of propriety!

367
00:25:30,605 --> 00:25:33,335
What could that smell be?

368
00:25:37,975 --> 00:25:39,105
You've gotten so thin.

369
00:25:45,345 --> 00:25:47,285
They say our bodies just rot when we die.

370
00:25:50,525 --> 00:25:51,725
But don't you worry.

371
00:25:52,255 --> 00:25:55,995
I'll make sure you're preserved perfectly
so you won't rot.

372
00:25:59,865 --> 00:26:01,935
Your stomach is completely empty,

373
00:26:02,535 --> 00:26:03,905
so you must feel nice and clean.

374
00:26:12,575 --> 00:26:14,145
Today's the big day.

375
00:26:15,575 --> 00:26:17,445
The glorious day you pass on.

376
00:26:23,355 --> 00:26:24,955
Should I show some mercy?

377
00:26:29,455 --> 00:26:33,425
I thought about letting you
starve to death peacefully.

378
00:26:35,495 --> 00:26:36,935
But that takes too long.

379
00:26:38,835 --> 00:26:40,575
And life clings on so stubbornly,
doesn't it?

380
00:26:42,135 --> 00:26:46,775
Besides, you need to feel at least
a fraction of what I went through.

381
00:26:46,775 --> 00:26:47,815
Don't you think?

382
00:26:50,015 --> 00:26:51,585
It's only fair.

383
00:26:54,285 --> 00:26:56,615
These last eight days
have been pure bliss.

384
00:26:57,385 --> 00:26:59,455
How should I send you off?

385
00:27:00,655 --> 00:27:02,795
How would you like to depart
from this world?

386
00:27:05,225 --> 00:27:08,735
You're going to beg me
to put you out of your misery.

387
00:27:09,365 --> 00:27:12,135
You know the saying.
"If you can't avoid it, enjoy it."

388
00:27:12,205 --> 00:27:13,365
So enjoy it.

389
00:27:15,935 --> 00:27:18,005
I'm about to become a monster.

390
00:27:18,975 --> 00:27:20,715
So watch this masterpiece unfold.

391
00:27:23,645 --> 00:27:25,515
And try to hold on to your sanity.

392
00:27:31,385 --> 00:27:32,485
Stop.

393
00:27:33,485 --> 00:27:35,955
Please! Don't kill me!

394
00:28:18,835 --> 00:28:20,435
Bring a few dishes. Your pick.

395
00:28:20,435 --> 00:28:21,775
We have to get the eggplant lasagna.

396
00:28:21,835 --> 00:28:22,835
Of course.

397
00:28:24,705 --> 00:28:27,415
CEO Hyun looks so young now.

398
00:28:27,475 --> 00:28:28,915
Did she say where she got her work done?

399
00:28:28,975 --> 00:28:31,815
- She looks so young in her photos.
- Tell me about it.

400
00:28:31,915 --> 00:28:34,715
I didn't ask. And I don't care to know.

401
00:28:34,785 --> 00:28:36,415
How could you not be curious
when you're an actress?

402
00:28:36,785 --> 00:28:38,825
Then again, you're still young enough
not to need it.

403
00:28:40,325 --> 00:28:43,325
How come there isn't a single crease
on your clothes?

404
00:28:43,395 --> 00:28:46,665
I changed before I left.
I was meeting you, Momo.

405
00:28:46,725 --> 00:28:49,765
I'm dying to see your beautiful place
that people have told me about.

406
00:28:50,095 --> 00:28:51,335
I moved.

407
00:28:52,035 --> 00:28:54,035
- To where?
- You wouldn't know if I told you.

408
00:28:54,035 --> 00:28:55,475
It's a residential-commercial spot.

409
00:28:56,175 --> 00:28:57,645
Momo, do you believe in fortune-telling?

410
00:28:58,175 --> 00:28:59,175
Should I?

411
00:28:59,175 --> 00:29:00,945
I kept getting sick and hurting myself.

412
00:29:00,945 --> 00:29:03,215
Something felt off, so I got a reading.

413
00:29:03,645 --> 00:29:06,485
Apparently, I'm not supposed to live
in a big, luxurious house.

414
00:29:06,615 --> 00:29:09,185
It's a pain, but that's my fate.

415
00:29:09,255 --> 00:29:11,155
- Oh my.
- So, what else could I do?

416
00:29:11,155 --> 00:29:12,825
Are you feeling better now?

417
00:29:12,885 --> 00:29:15,155
- Strangely enough, I am.
- Goodness.

418
00:29:22,765 --> 00:29:24,005
(An Hee)

419
00:29:26,865 --> 00:29:30,375
- Hey, An Hee.
- Why do you sound so down?

420
00:29:30,435 --> 00:29:31,705
I'm not down.

421
00:29:33,175 --> 00:29:36,315
Actually, I just stopped by your place,
but the lights were out.

422
00:29:36,715 --> 00:29:38,885
Why didn't you call first?
You shouldn't have come when you're busy.

423
00:29:39,545 --> 00:29:40,755
I just figured you'd be home.

424
00:29:40,885 --> 00:29:43,115
Perfect. I'll treat you,
so bring Jin Ju and come on over.

425
00:29:43,255 --> 00:29:45,585
She usually doesn't get off
until 10 p.m. or so.

426
00:29:47,025 --> 00:29:49,195
- Hey.
- Yes?

427
00:29:52,295 --> 00:29:55,135
Never mind. I'll tell you in person.
Where are you?

428
00:29:56,165 --> 00:29:58,265
I got a special bonus from the chairman.

429
00:29:58,405 --> 00:29:59,605
Use it to get yourself a car.

430
00:30:01,275 --> 00:30:03,135
All the other reporters have cars,
you know.

431
00:30:03,905 --> 00:30:05,545
Plenty of reporters don't.

432
00:30:09,045 --> 00:30:11,185
Then at least get a sofa
for your apartment or something.

433
00:30:11,985 --> 00:30:13,785
It's a palace even without a sofa.

434
00:30:17,955 --> 00:30:19,725
You'll never guess who
I interviewed today.

435
00:30:21,225 --> 00:30:22,595
Ha Yong Joong.

436
00:30:26,565 --> 00:30:27,695
Did he recognize you?

437
00:30:29,035 --> 00:30:30,495
I was filling in for a senior reporter.

438
00:30:30,765 --> 00:30:32,805
And he just pretended to look at my card.

439
00:30:35,875 --> 00:30:37,805
You've both done well for yourselves.
You should reach out to him.

440
00:30:38,545 --> 00:30:41,145
- "Done well?"
- You're not doing too badly yourself.

441
00:30:41,215 --> 00:30:43,545
It's good manners not to bother friends
after they've made it big.

442
00:30:47,315 --> 00:30:51,185
I'm so sick of Peoples.
There's just nowhere else decent to go.

443
00:30:51,625 --> 00:30:54,825
What do you mean there's nowhere to go?
You like Japanese food.

444
00:30:54,895 --> 00:30:57,125
Today, I'm treating you, Momo,

445
00:30:57,325 --> 00:30:59,425
but my clients usually pay.

446
00:30:59,725 --> 00:31:01,935
So how can I suggest we go
to some expensive omakase place?

447
00:31:01,935 --> 00:31:03,935
Besides, we're done talking business
in 20 or 30 minutes.

448
00:31:04,365 --> 00:31:07,775
And you can't just sit there on your phone
in silence for 2 or 3 hours.

449
00:31:09,505 --> 00:31:12,645
Confirm the facts tomorrow,
add some details, and run it.

450
00:31:13,005 --> 00:31:14,045
Understood.

451
00:31:14,115 --> 00:31:17,685
And this isn't like you, Geum Ba Ra.
You should've gotten a picture.

452
00:31:17,745 --> 00:31:19,685
I heard Ha Yong Joong is
quite a looker, too.

453
00:31:20,245 --> 00:31:22,685
It felt like he would've just walked out
if I forced the issue.

454
00:31:22,755 --> 00:31:24,185
He's that touchy?

455
00:31:24,885 --> 00:31:26,955
He said he wasn't comfortable
with being recognized.

456
00:31:27,525 --> 00:31:29,355
All right. You can go.

457
00:31:29,695 --> 00:31:30,695
Yes, sir.

458
00:31:36,835 --> 00:31:37,965
It's torture.

459
00:31:38,105 --> 00:31:40,105
And why are the explanations
for each dish so long?

460
00:31:40,465 --> 00:31:42,775
- Especially at fine-dining restaurants.
- I know, right?

461
00:31:43,175 --> 00:31:44,745
I wish they'd just stop.

462
00:31:44,945 --> 00:31:47,075
But it would be awkward to tell them to.

463
00:31:50,215 --> 00:31:51,315
Ba Ra!

464
00:31:57,055 --> 00:32:01,455
That last shoot was disappointing.
Can't we find a better photographer?

465
00:32:01,925 --> 00:32:03,395
I'm so sorry.
I must have the wrong room...

466
00:32:03,455 --> 00:32:04,865
Hello, Reporter Geum.

467
00:32:05,795 --> 00:32:07,395
You remember me?

468
00:32:07,765 --> 00:32:09,965
Of course. You're from Sungwoo Daily.

469
00:32:10,635 --> 00:32:11,965
Come on in for a second.

470
00:32:13,335 --> 00:32:14,335
Please.

471
00:32:18,845 --> 00:32:20,205
You didn't recognize me?

472
00:32:20,475 --> 00:32:21,875
How could I possibly not recognize you?

473
00:32:22,415 --> 00:32:24,745
I was at the last press conference too.

474
00:32:24,745 --> 00:32:25,845
I know.

475
00:32:26,315 --> 00:32:27,985
Then why didn't you say hi?

476
00:32:28,415 --> 00:32:29,955
I didn't want to interrupt.

477
00:32:30,825 --> 00:32:32,685
This is our director, and my manager.

478
00:32:35,055 --> 00:32:38,065
- I'm Choi Do Il.
- I'm all out of business cards.

479
00:32:38,125 --> 00:32:39,395
I'll get one next time.

480
00:32:40,525 --> 00:32:43,295
I've been meaning to contact you.

481
00:32:43,735 --> 00:32:45,405
You wrote such a wonderful article.

482
00:32:46,005 --> 00:32:48,335
I just wrote what I honestly felt.

483
00:32:48,975 --> 00:32:52,345
You should be an actress
instead of a reporter.

484
00:32:52,405 --> 00:32:53,445
Right, Director?

485
00:32:53,445 --> 00:32:55,575
You say that as if you really mean it.

486
00:32:55,675 --> 00:32:57,785
And you're taking my sincerity as a joke.

487
00:33:01,285 --> 00:33:04,055
My friend is here.

488
00:33:04,055 --> 00:33:06,155
I'll buy you a meal to thank you.

489
00:33:06,225 --> 00:33:07,695
I could treat you instead.

490
00:33:18,965 --> 00:33:21,305
I tend to walk into the wrong rooms.

491
00:33:21,375 --> 00:33:23,475
I've even walked into the men's restroom.

492
00:33:24,145 --> 00:33:25,445
Oh, my gosh. Me too!

493
00:33:25,575 --> 00:33:27,845
I've walked into the ladies' room twice.

494
00:33:28,745 --> 00:33:30,715
You should stop by our company sometime,

495
00:33:31,045 --> 00:33:33,145
like for a party or a formal event.

496
00:33:33,245 --> 00:33:34,685
I'll doll you up.

497
00:33:35,985 --> 00:33:38,285
I can already picture
the perfect outfits for you.

498
00:33:39,885 --> 00:33:40,925
(Sungwoo Daily, Geum Ba Ra)

499
00:33:41,055 --> 00:33:42,855
That's very kind of you to say.

500
00:33:42,855 --> 00:33:44,995
He doesn't make empty promises.

501
00:33:45,165 --> 00:33:46,225
Sometimes I do.

502
00:33:48,595 --> 00:33:50,635
Hold on, your outfits...

503
00:33:53,505 --> 00:33:54,975
Look, we're twinning.

504
00:33:55,905 --> 00:33:58,445
This outfit was originally hers,
but we swapped.

505
00:33:58,505 --> 00:34:00,245
You two look great together.

506
00:34:00,305 --> 00:34:02,145
And she's an incredible writer.

507
00:34:02,245 --> 00:34:05,285
To use an old-fashioned phrase,
you've got both style and skill.

508
00:34:05,715 --> 00:34:07,285
And what's your personality like?

509
00:34:09,155 --> 00:34:11,655
- I'll get out of your hair.
- No, wait...

510
00:34:11,725 --> 00:34:12,955
I'll text you.

511
00:34:14,555 --> 00:34:16,095
Please do stop by.

512
00:34:18,165 --> 00:34:19,495
An answer, please.

513
00:34:19,895 --> 00:34:20,895
Okay.

514
00:34:39,185 --> 00:34:41,685
She's a breath of fresh air. So unique.

515
00:34:41,955 --> 00:34:43,015
Isn't she?

516
00:34:43,355 --> 00:34:44,355
Yes.

517
00:34:44,485 --> 00:34:48,455
At the press conference for "Magic Fog,"
she nailed the key points of the project,

518
00:34:48,595 --> 00:34:50,425
and she wrote about me so beautifully.

519
00:34:50,625 --> 00:34:52,525
You could feel her respect for actors.

520
00:34:52,995 --> 00:34:56,295
And to think, she was just typing quietly
and barely asked any questions.

521
00:34:56,365 --> 00:34:58,805
You know what they say,
still waters run deep.

522
00:34:59,065 --> 00:35:00,365
Is that a real saying?

523
00:35:00,365 --> 00:35:02,675
Half of what he says are old sayings.

524
00:35:02,735 --> 00:35:05,745
Don't differentiate between old and new.
That's all just judgment.

525
00:35:05,975 --> 00:35:07,975
Do you know what happens
when you let go of judgment?

526
00:35:07,975 --> 00:35:09,345
What?

527
00:35:09,845 --> 00:35:12,385
Manager Yoon, you're really knocking them
back tonight.

528
00:35:12,885 --> 00:35:15,085
- Enlightenment.
- You've reached enlightenment?

529
00:35:15,155 --> 00:35:16,385
I'm on the verge.

530
00:35:17,555 --> 00:35:20,825
That's why I don't get stressed.
I just shake everything off.

531
00:35:24,225 --> 00:35:27,735
- Compliments of the chef.
- Oh, my.

532
00:35:27,995 --> 00:35:30,865
- But I'm so full.
- There's always room for dessert.

533
00:35:31,305 --> 00:35:33,905
- Please thank the chef for me.
- Will do.

534
00:35:34,775 --> 00:35:36,405
Gosh, this looks amazing.

535
00:35:36,405 --> 00:35:38,205
I should come with you more often, Momo.

536
00:35:38,275 --> 00:35:39,475
We even get freebies like this.

537
00:35:39,875 --> 00:35:42,345
When I come with other people,
they don't even give me a cabbage heart.

538
00:35:43,645 --> 00:35:44,785
A digestive.

539
00:35:45,115 --> 00:35:46,185
Thank you.

540
00:35:49,485 --> 00:35:51,285
And what's a "cabbage heart?"

541
00:35:51,585 --> 00:35:53,325
- Do you know?
- No?

542
00:35:53,325 --> 00:35:54,795
You can search online for it.

543
00:35:56,625 --> 00:35:59,795
It's the sweet core of the cabbage.
It's actually pretty tasty.

544
00:36:00,325 --> 00:36:03,735
- We're going to have leftovers.
- Says who? My pouch.

545
00:36:06,435 --> 00:36:08,705
You can't let food go to waste.

546
00:36:09,005 --> 00:36:12,075
- Are you getting a doggy bag?
- This will last me two days.

547
00:36:12,145 --> 00:36:15,645
- You're so thrifty.
- Call me Mr. Thrifty.

548
00:36:17,715 --> 00:36:21,855
Teacher, whoever marries you
will be a very lucky woman.

549
00:36:21,985 --> 00:36:23,285
In what way?

550
00:36:23,355 --> 00:36:27,085
In every way.
You're so considerate and funny.

551
00:36:27,155 --> 00:36:29,955
Enough with the lip service.
Set me up with someone.

552
00:36:30,295 --> 00:36:32,295
But all I know are other actors.

553
00:36:32,295 --> 00:36:34,435
What's wrong with actresses?
I'd be grateful.

554
00:36:34,565 --> 00:36:36,095
They're pretty and they make good money.

555
00:36:36,165 --> 00:36:38,535
As if you don't know
way more actresses than I do.

556
00:36:38,835 --> 00:36:41,175
And they're all trying to get
on your good side.

557
00:36:41,235 --> 00:36:43,975
- A barber can't cut his own hair.
- So looks are important to you?

558
00:36:44,035 --> 00:36:46,205
For him, it's looks first,
and looks second.

559
00:36:46,275 --> 00:36:49,315
You're wrong. First is looks, second is...

560
00:36:53,645 --> 00:36:55,955
My little brother is a watermelon fiend.

561
00:36:56,155 --> 00:36:59,255
In his heyday, he could eat
almost a whole one in a single sitting.

562
00:36:59,325 --> 00:37:01,755
- You have a brother?
- He's young enough to be his son.

563
00:37:02,355 --> 00:37:04,325
Not with a 17-year age gap.

564
00:37:04,595 --> 00:37:05,765
By the way,

565
00:37:06,325 --> 00:37:08,865
there's actually someone
who wants to be set up with you, Momo.

566
00:37:09,565 --> 00:37:11,005
And I can vouch for him.

567
00:37:11,305 --> 00:37:13,935
He's the Noir Hospital chairman's son,
the chief surgeon.

568
00:37:13,935 --> 00:37:15,175
And there's the Noir Foundation,

569
00:37:15,175 --> 00:37:17,105
so he's the total package, in every way.

570
00:37:17,105 --> 00:37:18,105
Oh, goodness.

571
00:37:18,175 --> 00:37:19,345
I'm not really into doctors.

572
00:37:19,405 --> 00:37:21,975
Why not? He's a prime catch.

573
00:37:21,975 --> 00:37:23,215
Who said anything about marriage?

574
00:37:23,345 --> 00:37:26,545
Just meet him, for now.
I've got my reputation to think about.

575
00:37:27,085 --> 00:37:30,015
Apparently, he was completely smitten
after watching "A Maiden's Prayer."

576
00:37:30,555 --> 00:37:32,385
Tell him I'm nothing like that
in real life.

577
00:37:32,755 --> 00:37:36,525
Prospect-wise, his younger brother
might be an even better catch.

578
00:37:37,425 --> 00:37:39,495
He has zero interest in women.

579
00:37:40,095 --> 00:37:41,295
So he's just a man on the outside?

580
00:37:41,435 --> 00:37:44,265
He must quit his video games first.

581
00:37:44,335 --> 00:37:46,035
Only then might he start noticing women.

582
00:37:56,215 --> 00:37:58,485
(Sungwoo Daily, Geum Ba Ra)

583
00:38:06,185 --> 00:38:07,185
What?

584
00:38:09,025 --> 00:38:10,025
Did you eat fish cakes?

585
00:38:12,065 --> 00:38:13,065
Can you smell it?

586
00:38:14,495 --> 00:38:15,595
Don't you brush your teeth after you eat?

587
00:38:56,975 --> 00:38:57,975
Thank you.

588
00:39:05,885 --> 00:39:06,915
Don't be late.

589
00:39:14,995 --> 00:39:16,225
Thanks for finding the time
when you were busy.

590
00:39:18,625 --> 00:39:19,665
The pleasure is all mine.

591
00:39:21,535 --> 00:39:22,535
The Noir Foundation...

592
00:39:22,935 --> 00:39:23,995
Yes.

593
00:39:24,335 --> 00:39:26,065
I've heard it does a lot of good work.

594
00:39:26,565 --> 00:39:27,565
Not me personally...

595
00:39:28,475 --> 00:39:29,475
It's the foundation that does the work.

596
00:39:30,705 --> 00:39:33,475
When things free up a bit,
I'd like to volunteer my talents, too.

597
00:39:35,715 --> 00:39:38,415
- That's very generous of you.
- I have to apologize.

598
00:39:39,045 --> 00:39:40,045
Alright.

599
00:39:40,145 --> 00:39:43,355
I just got a call for a sudden reshoot,
so I won't be able to stay for dinner.

600
00:39:44,455 --> 00:39:45,455
I'm so sorry.

601
00:39:46,755 --> 00:39:47,755
Do you have to leave right now?

602
00:39:50,155 --> 00:39:52,165
I can stay for one drink, though.

603
00:39:56,995 --> 00:39:58,865
- You're filming a period drama?
- Yes.

604
00:39:59,635 --> 00:40:01,905
It's just an over-the-shoulder shot.
I only need to deliver my lines.

605
00:40:02,405 --> 00:40:04,305
I already spoke with the manager
on my way in.

606
00:40:04,675 --> 00:40:05,675
If I'd known,

607
00:40:06,605 --> 00:40:08,245
I would've had a decent lunch.

608
00:40:08,845 --> 00:40:09,845
Oh, no.

609
00:40:11,015 --> 00:40:12,015
I was busy, too, though.

610
00:40:15,685 --> 00:40:16,685
I understand.

611
00:40:17,085 --> 00:40:19,425
Because when I get paged for an emergency,
I have to leave immediately, too.

612
00:40:29,365 --> 00:40:30,595
Anyway, at least...

613
00:40:31,605 --> 00:40:32,605
I got to see you.

614
00:40:34,005 --> 00:40:36,275
"Got to see you?"
Not "It's an honor to see you?"

615
00:40:45,245 --> 00:40:46,645
I like this champagne.

616
00:40:47,285 --> 00:40:49,285
I'll send a few bottles to your place.
I know the address.

617
00:40:49,815 --> 00:40:51,155
No, that's okay. I already have some.

618
00:40:51,655 --> 00:40:54,125
So when can we reschedule the dinner
we missed tonight?

619
00:40:55,055 --> 00:40:57,225
I don't make personal plans
when I'm working on a project.

620
00:40:58,365 --> 00:41:00,665
- Is that a no?
- It's not a no.

621
00:41:01,395 --> 00:41:02,895
This is just how I live.

622
00:41:04,935 --> 00:41:06,465
A normal life is impossible for me.

623
00:41:06,465 --> 00:41:07,875
You can always make time.

624
00:41:10,405 --> 00:41:11,475
No matter how busy you are,

625
00:41:12,075 --> 00:41:14,145
everyone has time for a meal or two a day.

626
00:41:17,045 --> 00:41:18,285
Am I that bad?

627
00:41:19,715 --> 00:41:21,555
Is he dropping the formalities?

628
00:41:23,285 --> 00:41:24,685
I haven't had the chance to find out.

629
00:41:24,985 --> 00:41:26,425
That's my point.
You should get to know me.

630
00:41:27,325 --> 00:41:28,795
Do you make a habit
of being so condescending?

631
00:41:30,595 --> 00:41:32,395
- To people in general?
- Yes.

632
00:41:33,425 --> 00:41:34,465
Well...

633
00:41:35,435 --> 00:41:36,695
Did you feel like
I was talking down to you?

634
00:41:37,035 --> 00:41:39,305
These days, people even speak politely
to preschoolers.

635
00:41:40,335 --> 00:41:41,375
I wasn't using casual language.

636
00:41:43,575 --> 00:41:44,575
I was being polite.

637
00:41:47,875 --> 00:41:49,645
My debut was in a medical drama,

638
00:41:49,915 --> 00:41:52,545
and the doctors who were our consultants
were incredibly busy.

639
00:41:53,245 --> 00:41:55,255
And yet, you've seen my show?

640
00:41:56,555 --> 00:41:57,685
Only "A Maiden's Prayer."

641
00:41:59,155 --> 00:42:01,055
I stumbled on it while flipping channels
and got completely hooked.

642
00:42:01,755 --> 00:42:02,895
I binged the whole thing in one day.

643
00:42:03,825 --> 00:42:04,825
And not on fast-forward.

644
00:42:06,025 --> 00:42:07,065
Doctor...

645
00:42:08,765 --> 00:42:09,965
This might sound a little forward, but...

646
00:42:13,705 --> 00:42:16,435
Your looks are kind of wasted
on just your patients.

647
00:42:17,235 --> 00:42:18,645
Have you ever been scouted?

648
00:42:21,515 --> 00:42:22,515
You have, haven't you?

649
00:42:23,475 --> 00:42:25,585
- I'm not the type at all.
- You never know.

650
00:42:26,385 --> 00:42:29,985
Being in front of a camera
can bring out a hidden talent.

651
00:42:32,255 --> 00:42:33,625
I'm supposed to take over the hospital.

652
00:42:35,525 --> 00:42:36,555
This is a much better fit for me.

653
00:42:37,395 --> 00:42:39,195
Let me guess, you picked a stethoscope
at your first birthday party?

654
00:42:39,965 --> 00:42:41,395
From the pictures,
it looks like I picked a dictionary.

655
00:42:42,465 --> 00:42:44,395
- What did you pick?
- A microphone.

656
00:42:47,005 --> 00:42:48,005
Although...

657
00:42:50,305 --> 00:42:51,305
Go on.

658
00:42:52,945 --> 00:42:56,415
If there had been a model of a skull,
I would've picked that.

659
00:42:59,345 --> 00:43:00,345
Come on.

660
00:43:01,115 --> 00:43:02,115
You can't be serious.

661
00:43:03,455 --> 00:43:04,985
When you operate,
you find every brain has its own feel.

662
00:43:05,825 --> 00:43:06,825
They're all different.

663
00:43:07,455 --> 00:43:08,455
Really?

664
00:43:09,525 --> 00:43:10,525
Yes.

665
00:43:14,295 --> 00:43:17,165
You don't want to open up my head, do you?

666
00:43:19,965 --> 00:43:20,965
Of course not.

667
00:43:22,405 --> 00:43:23,405
Let's hope that never has to happen.

668
00:43:25,245 --> 00:43:27,105
You look good when you smile.

669
00:43:28,875 --> 00:43:32,445
You should smile more often.
Your first impression was a bit stiff.

670
00:43:34,415 --> 00:43:35,415
That's a first.

671
00:43:36,155 --> 00:43:37,155
Really?

672
00:43:37,515 --> 00:43:39,085
I've been called arrogant
a few times, though.

673
00:43:39,325 --> 00:43:41,855
By who? Your friends?

674
00:43:44,825 --> 00:43:45,825
Then give me a chance.

675
00:43:46,865 --> 00:43:48,295
A chance to show you my smile more often.

676
00:43:58,245 --> 00:44:01,575
Playing my role in "A Maiden's Prayer"
was honestly brutal.

677
00:44:02,745 --> 00:44:04,785
But I got way too invested
in the character.

678
00:44:11,055 --> 00:44:14,925
From a man's perspective,
did you relate to the older man at all?

679
00:44:20,495 --> 00:44:21,495
Are you asking if I'm a pervert?

680
00:44:23,465 --> 00:44:24,465
No.

681
00:44:25,835 --> 00:44:28,575
I was just curious
what male viewers thought of him.

682
00:44:29,375 --> 00:44:31,275
His inner thoughts? His base instincts?

683
00:44:33,405 --> 00:44:35,115
I suppose a very small minority
might have related.

684
00:44:35,915 --> 00:44:37,145
People like that do exist, after all.

685
00:44:37,975 --> 00:44:39,645
But people should live
like decent human beings.

686
00:44:42,785 --> 00:44:43,785
To behold you in the flesh...

687
00:44:44,785 --> 00:44:46,285
Oh, my gosh,
did I really just say "behold?"

688
00:44:46,625 --> 00:44:47,655
I must have shattered your fantasy.

689
00:44:48,595 --> 00:44:52,625
I looked pure in "A Maiden's Prayer,"
thanks to the director.

690
00:44:54,225 --> 00:44:55,595
This side of you is charming too.

691
00:44:56,235 --> 00:44:57,265
What's the role?

692
00:44:58,435 --> 00:45:00,505
- The queen of the social scene.
- So you're playing yourself.

693
00:45:01,575 --> 00:45:02,575
Are you a social butterfly?

694
00:45:06,475 --> 00:45:08,575
- I'm not so sure.
- About me?

695
00:45:09,275 --> 00:45:10,345
Or about women in general?

696
00:45:13,285 --> 00:45:14,685
Do you know a lot about men?

697
00:45:15,755 --> 00:45:16,755
I'd like to think so.

698
00:45:19,385 --> 00:45:20,385
I should get going.

699
00:45:23,955 --> 00:45:24,965
I'll give you a ride.

700
00:45:25,425 --> 00:45:26,965
- Where's the set?
- No, thanks.

701
00:45:27,025 --> 00:45:28,025
The van's more comfortable.

702
00:45:32,735 --> 00:45:34,165
So when are we having
this dinner we couldn't have?

703
00:45:34,405 --> 00:45:36,435
Would a meal taste any good
if it feels like an obligation?

704
00:45:38,205 --> 00:45:40,005
If there's one thing
you should know about me,

705
00:45:40,945 --> 00:45:43,575
I'm a total mama's girl.

706
00:45:45,185 --> 00:45:46,185
And?

707
00:45:46,715 --> 00:45:47,715
Just thought you should know.

708
00:45:48,985 --> 00:45:51,215
I'm not as charming as the characters
I play in dramas.

709
00:45:52,585 --> 00:45:53,655
In that case,

710
00:45:54,325 --> 00:45:56,925
I'm an only child, and a daddy's boy.

711
00:47:11,365 --> 00:47:14,435
(6 Months After Momo's Accident)

712
00:47:14,435 --> 00:47:15,535
(Hospital Director, Shin Ju Shin)

713
00:47:22,045 --> 00:47:26,145
(Kim Jin Ju)

714
00:47:34,425 --> 00:47:36,555
(Hospital Director, Shin Ju Shin)

715
00:47:36,795 --> 00:47:37,795
You're here.

716
00:47:39,625 --> 00:47:41,025
I heard the surgery was over.

717
00:47:54,045 --> 00:47:56,245
(Should I prepare your dinner?)

718
00:47:59,015 --> 00:48:00,015
You should have some dinner.

719
00:48:02,355 --> 00:48:03,355
This is enough for me.

720
00:48:05,225 --> 00:48:06,485
I don't have the appetite.

721
00:48:10,025 --> 00:48:11,025
Don't bother.

722
00:48:28,875 --> 00:48:29,945
Do you still have rounds?

723
00:48:32,745 --> 00:48:33,785
Do you have to go see your patients?

724
00:48:45,495 --> 00:48:47,465
I think it was about a month...

725
00:48:48,765 --> 00:48:50,435
before your father passed away?

726
00:48:54,935 --> 00:48:55,975
I heard about it.

727
00:48:56,775 --> 00:48:58,135
I didn't tell anyone.

728
00:49:00,175 --> 00:49:01,445
I heard...

729
00:49:02,315 --> 00:49:03,545
a brain swap is possible.

730
00:49:05,285 --> 00:49:06,285
You've done one, haven't you?

731
00:49:11,725 --> 00:49:14,725
I've thought this through,
and it's the only way.

732
00:49:16,655 --> 00:49:18,665
It's only a matter of time
before the world finds out.

733
00:49:19,825 --> 00:49:21,065
How long can we hide this?

734
00:49:23,735 --> 00:49:24,835
And I can't...

735
00:49:28,105 --> 00:49:29,505
bear to see this anymore as her mother.

736
00:49:33,205 --> 00:49:34,875
I'm sure you feel the same way,
Director Shin.

737
00:49:42,955 --> 00:49:44,885
You must have considered the option,
haven't you?

738
00:49:46,985 --> 00:49:47,985
We'd need a subject.

739
00:49:54,425 --> 00:49:55,435
Me.

740
00:50:05,675 --> 00:50:09,445
I've considered every possible option,
but dying isn't the answer.

741
00:50:10,015 --> 00:50:12,645
I can't just die alone.
Am I supposed to poison my sweet girl?

742
00:50:13,385 --> 00:50:16,215
Could I give Momo a lethal injection?

743
00:50:19,485 --> 00:50:20,555
I'm not giving up.

744
00:50:23,025 --> 00:50:24,695
I'll take care of any problems or issues.

745
00:50:24,695 --> 00:50:26,225
I will handle everything.

746
00:50:28,735 --> 00:50:29,765
Just do the surgery.

747
00:50:29,965 --> 00:50:31,365
Just because it was successful once...

748
00:50:33,435 --> 00:50:34,605
Things can still go wrong.

749
00:50:34,865 --> 00:50:37,535
There's always a risk with surgery.

750
00:50:37,935 --> 00:50:39,545
That's why you have us sign consent forms.

751
00:50:40,345 --> 00:50:41,575
But what if something goes wrong,

752
00:50:42,915 --> 00:50:44,145
and you don't wake up?

753
00:50:44,215 --> 00:50:45,645
Could it be any worse than this?

754
00:50:46,645 --> 00:50:48,885
Just being awake and breathing
is already torment for me.

755
00:50:49,955 --> 00:50:51,985
I haven't gone a single night
without crying myself to sleep.

756
00:50:55,455 --> 00:50:57,055
I don't care if I end up like Momo.

757
00:50:58,295 --> 00:51:01,065
Just do it. We'll leave the rest to fate.

758
00:51:02,635 --> 00:51:04,395
Your engagement isn't public knowledge,

759
00:51:05,105 --> 00:51:07,005
so I can just live as Momo,

760
00:51:07,805 --> 00:51:09,575
and you'll be free to meet someone new.

761
00:51:10,105 --> 00:51:11,705
People's feelings change, after all.

762
00:51:12,905 --> 00:51:14,405
Some feelings don't change.

763
00:51:16,845 --> 00:51:17,845
I doubt that.

764
00:51:19,385 --> 00:51:22,215
If I collapse from the stress of all this,
who will take care of Momo?

765
00:51:22,455 --> 00:51:25,055
You know what they say.
"When illness comes in, love flies out."

766
00:51:26,125 --> 00:51:27,685
The feelings you've developed
in just over a year?

767
00:51:28,185 --> 00:51:30,795
It wasn't love.
It was just an infatuation.

768
00:51:30,795 --> 00:51:33,325
- We...
- The ocean may never run dry,

769
00:51:33,325 --> 00:51:34,765
but fire always burns out.

770
00:51:34,995 --> 00:51:36,735
What fire burns forever?

771
00:51:42,135 --> 00:51:43,575
I loved Momo more than anyone
in the world.

772
00:51:47,805 --> 00:51:49,445
My love for her is no less
than your love as a mother.

773
00:51:49,515 --> 00:51:52,415
Are you comparing a mother's love
to romantic love?

774
00:51:53,315 --> 00:51:55,255
Okay, sure. Let's say it was love,
up until now.

775
00:51:55,615 --> 00:51:57,085
But you'd just leave her in this state?

776
00:51:57,815 --> 00:51:59,525
If you were in Momo's condition,

777
00:51:59,525 --> 00:52:01,685
what would she have wanted for you?

778
00:52:02,395 --> 00:52:04,195
Is just being alive the same as living?

779
00:52:10,795 --> 00:52:12,405
Let's just think about Momo.

780
00:52:15,205 --> 00:52:17,835
Let's think about what's really
and truly best for her.

781
00:52:22,215 --> 00:52:24,315
All you have to do is transplant
her brain into my body.

782
00:52:26,315 --> 00:52:28,215
Her eyes, her nose, her mouth...

783
00:52:29,085 --> 00:52:30,315
They'll all be the same.

784
00:52:32,185 --> 00:52:33,425
The damaged brain?

785
00:52:34,755 --> 00:52:37,155
If it's in her body or mine,
what's the difference?

786
00:52:44,565 --> 00:52:45,805
This is what a parent...

787
00:52:48,875 --> 00:52:50,135
This is a mother's love.

788
00:53:09,525 --> 00:53:10,855
Chairman Hwang of Bada Group.

789
00:53:12,125 --> 00:53:15,565
The body is Chairman Hwang's,
but the brain is his son's.

790
00:53:17,065 --> 00:53:18,835
The father had a terminal brain tumor,

791
00:53:20,135 --> 00:53:23,535
while his prized only son was paralyzed
in a motorcycle accident.

792
00:53:25,245 --> 00:53:28,375
After your father told me,
I watched him closely.

793
00:53:29,875 --> 00:53:32,485
The way Chairman Hwang talked,
and his whole demeanor...

794
00:53:33,645 --> 00:53:35,185
Only his face looked like
he was in his 60s.

795
00:53:50,635 --> 00:53:51,635
Leave it.

796
00:53:55,635 --> 00:53:57,775
Skin needs to stay moisturized.

797
00:53:58,645 --> 00:53:59,645
Hey.

798
00:54:01,245 --> 00:54:02,445
Thank you for all your hard work.

799
00:54:05,715 --> 00:54:08,685
You've worked hard.
It's time to take a vacation.

800
00:54:10,085 --> 00:54:11,855
You've never been to Hong Kong, have you?

801
00:54:11,855 --> 00:54:13,055
You should go. It's nice.

802
00:54:14,185 --> 00:54:15,525
I'll book you a business class flight.

803
00:54:16,295 --> 00:54:18,395
But I'm not planning on leaving.

804
00:54:18,695 --> 00:54:20,765
You told me I could stay
for as long as I wanted.

805
00:54:22,735 --> 00:54:24,735
I've been diagnosed with depression.

806
00:54:25,435 --> 00:54:26,505
So I need to do something.

807
00:54:26,965 --> 00:54:28,775
I'm thinking of trying to do
some housework myself.

808
00:54:29,775 --> 00:54:30,935
Something physical.

809
00:54:32,205 --> 00:54:34,175
But how could you, ma'am?

810
00:56:36,735 --> 00:56:39,505
(Current time, Surgery time,
Anesthesia time)

811
00:58:16,595 --> 00:58:17,735
One thing's missing.

812
00:58:25,205 --> 00:58:26,205
The candles.

813
00:58:27,145 --> 00:58:28,145
The wind blew them out.

814
00:58:28,975 --> 00:58:30,045
This is more than enough.

815
00:58:32,615 --> 00:58:35,215
So, is that necklace special or something?

816
00:58:35,915 --> 00:58:36,985
You're just now asking?

817
00:58:39,755 --> 00:58:41,055
It protects me.

818
00:58:41,955 --> 00:58:44,455
From now on,
I'll be the one to protect you.

819
00:58:44,795 --> 00:58:46,625
But I thought you were afraid of water.

820
00:58:48,095 --> 00:58:49,095
It's for when I'm underwater.

821
00:58:50,435 --> 00:58:51,735
I'm going to take up scuba diving.

822
00:58:52,465 --> 00:58:53,465
Really?

823
00:58:53,965 --> 00:58:55,205
I want us to do everything together.

824
00:58:56,605 --> 00:58:57,605
Who gave it to you?

825
00:58:59,175 --> 00:59:01,245
- My instructor.
- Your scuba instructor?

826
00:59:01,305 --> 00:59:02,315
Yes.

827
00:59:03,215 --> 00:59:04,215
Take it off.

828
00:59:06,045 --> 00:59:09,415
Take it off. I'll have a prettier one
made for you, with a diamond.

829
00:59:10,785 --> 00:59:11,785
Are you jealous?

830
00:59:12,785 --> 00:59:14,285
Then don't give me a reason to be.

831
00:59:15,055 --> 00:59:16,425
What did I do?

832
00:59:19,495 --> 00:59:20,495
My buddy...

833
00:59:21,095 --> 00:59:22,165
My diving partner.

834
00:59:22,895 --> 00:59:24,095
Your buddy must be a man, right?

835
00:59:24,695 --> 00:59:25,705
She's a woman.

836
00:59:33,105 --> 00:59:36,045
I first thought
you had great manners at Crystal.

837
00:59:36,545 --> 00:59:39,585
We were talking about acting,
and when I raised my champagne glass,

838
00:59:39,985 --> 00:59:41,815
you raised yours with me to drink.

839
00:59:52,155 --> 00:59:53,165
That's just common courtesy.

840
00:59:53,765 --> 00:59:55,665
It wasn't just manners.
It came from the heart.

841
00:59:56,835 --> 00:59:59,465
I love how thoughtful you are
about the little things.

842
01:00:15,145 --> 01:00:16,785
I want to be just like my dad.

843
01:00:18,055 --> 01:00:21,285
He could easily meet younger women
and remarry,

844
01:00:23,695 --> 01:00:25,025
but he only ever thinks about my mother.

845
01:00:26,365 --> 01:00:27,765
He's always been that devoted.

846
01:00:29,935 --> 01:00:30,935
Do you believe in a next life?

847
01:00:32,935 --> 01:00:34,765
I wouldn't rule it out.

848
01:00:36,835 --> 01:00:37,975
If there is a next life,

849
01:00:38,805 --> 01:00:40,805
he says he'll find my mother
and marry her all over again.

850
01:00:42,945 --> 01:00:44,645
But missing someone is different
from being lonely.

851
01:00:45,045 --> 01:00:47,585
Don't you think he'll get lonely
when he's older?

852
01:00:48,585 --> 01:00:49,855
He'll have his grandchildren to dote on.

853
01:00:52,355 --> 01:00:53,755
It isn't love if it changes.

854
01:01:01,665 --> 01:01:02,665
You have to stay...

855
01:01:03,865 --> 01:01:05,065
by my side forever.

856
01:01:59,955 --> 01:02:02,825
(Doctor Shin)

857
01:02:03,155 --> 01:02:04,395
What happened to Momo?

858
01:02:04,755 --> 01:02:05,765
Who told you?

859
01:02:05,825 --> 01:02:08,795
Someone made 100 million dollars
just by developing one game.

860
01:02:08,995 --> 01:02:09,995
This is Ha Yong Joong.

861
01:02:10,135 --> 01:02:11,535
I was wondering if you were...

862
01:02:11,635 --> 01:02:14,235
the Geum Ba Ra at Minjin Elementary
16 years ago.

863
01:02:14,235 --> 01:02:15,335
You have a boyfriend, right?

864
01:02:15,435 --> 01:02:17,235
What makes you think I do?

865
01:02:17,235 --> 01:02:19,075
I made a point not to ask you the same.

866
01:02:19,145 --> 01:02:20,305
Why didn't you ask on purpose?

867
01:02:20,305 --> 01:02:21,345
I think I want to get married.

868
01:02:21,405 --> 01:02:24,545
- To me?
- Just give me a chance to prove myself.

869
01:02:24,615 --> 01:02:26,715
- He's actually not bad.
- If he contacts you, shut him down.

870
01:02:26,985 --> 01:02:28,885
So he doesn't get his hopes up.
Don't lead him on.

871
01:02:29,355 --> 01:02:32,555
My mother left this for me
to give to the person I fell in love with.

872
01:02:32,755 --> 01:02:34,555
He's really determined, isn't he?

873
01:02:34,555 --> 01:02:35,755
I want to share my whole life with you.

874
01:02:35,825 --> 01:02:36,925
But I don't.

875
01:02:36,925 --> 01:02:38,155
Then I'll become your everything.

876
01:02:38,955 --> 01:02:40,565
I can promise and swear to you.

877
01:02:40,765 --> 01:02:43,265
I know I can be a responsible husband.

878
01:02:43,535 --> 01:02:46,135
How about an engagement first,
rather than marriage?

879
01:02:49,835 --> 01:02:51,835
(Subtitles are provided by KOCOWA.)
